57,0.01719472,-0.07343819,0.00221707,-0.03324480,-0.02563062,0.09233899,0.04503682,0.01661205,0.04141185,0.08191865,0.03573146,0.05124380,-0.08249718,-0.04484628,0.00328862,-0.00956142,-0.01277564,0.01533781,0.01770602,-0.00936252,-0.02602812,-0.02847404,0.01198076,-0.00329821,0.06784593,-0.00064522,-0.01852701,0.00452489,-0.01188780,0.00242456,-0.07144609,0.02492276,0.05369787,-0.03793183,-0.03732285,-0.02590400,0.01618559,0.01892573,-0.02672455,-0.00175848,0.06285431,0.01835335]',E'Passing JSX as children {/*passing-jsx-as-children*/}\n\n```css\n.card {\n  width: fit-content;\n  margin: 5px;\n  padding: 5px;\n  font-size: 20px;\n  text-align: center;\n  border: 1px solid #aaa;\n  border-radius: 20px;\n  background: #fff;\n}\n.avatar {\n  margin: 20px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n}\n```\n\n</Sandpack>\n\nTry replacing the `<Avatar>` inside `<Card>` with some text to see how the `Card` component can wrap any nested content. It doesn''t need to "know" what''s being rendered inside of it. You will see this flexible pattern in many places.','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Passing Props To A Component", "section_title": "passing-props-to-a-component", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/passing-props-to-a-component.md", "topics": "react,hooks,passing,props,to,a,component", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
