744,0.04454700,0.01645430,0.00024753,0.01698157,0.01575669,0.06240828,0.02872901,-0.02130971,-0.00452583,-0.01665223,-0.01176299,-0.00313912,-0.06818524,-0.05850716,0.03373458,0.00786892,0.00537523,-0.01159582,0.00458470,0.06107235,0.01449791,0.00831116,-0.09551370,-0.04688584,-0.03983825,-0.10551514,0.01482963,-0.04337782,0.01436666,0.01719345,-0.05791731,-0.03788265,-0.00791845,-0.02491521,0.02077235,-0.01259120,-0.00925923,0.01950248,0.00217140,0.08052694,-0.00361195,0.03455640]',E'Step 1: Declare an Effect {/*step-1-declare-an-effect*/}\n\nTo declare an Effect in your component, import the [`useEffect` Hook](/reference/react/useEffect) from React:\n\n```js\nimport { useEffect } from ''react'';\n```\n\nThen, call it at the top level of your component and put some code inside your Effect:\n\n```js {2-4}\nfunction MyComponent() {\n  useEffect(() => {\n    // Code here will run after *every* render\n  });\n  return <div />;\n}\n```','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
