358,-0.01123488,0.00371164,0.01753415,-0.01189946,-0.02380204,0.06990783,-0.02348697,-0.06600326,-0.01194000,0.01763925,-0.02541245,0.02510234,-0.05627536,-0.02569200,0.02284814,-0.02674534,0.01150316,0.02963561,0.00096663,0.06293306,0.02302040,0.05214826,-0.03013283,0.02869035,0.02878992,-0.08389544,-0.00928430,-0.05631930,0.02450215,0.00566108,-0.02446400,-0.03318253,0.04918457,-0.05210358,0.03251252,0.02868360,-0.00278993,0.02551133,-0.02847946,0.03981953,-0.01354554,0.06941519]',E'Step 1: Declare an Effect {/*step-1-declare-an-effect*/}\n\nThe solution here is to **wrap the side effect with `useEffect` to move it out of the rendering calculation:**\n\n```js {6,12}\nimport { useEffect, useRef } from ''react'';\n\nfunction VideoPlayer({ src, isPlaying }) {\n  const ref = useRef(null);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (isPlaying) {\n      ref.current.play();\n    } else {\n      ref.current.pause();\n    }\n  });\n\n  return <video ref={ref} src={src} loop playsInline />;\n}\n```','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
