386920,0.02344158,-0.02889472,-0.02724972,0.00452391,0.02558821,0.00196061,0.03671851,-0.06229770,-0.00324332,0.04829798,0.02743553,-0.00622340,-0.02590994,-0.04659109,0.02187591,-0.00635194,0.02796077,-0.05756150,0.01354061,0.02903397,0.01878083,0.07750983,-0.10928043,-0.03975810,-0.05748576,-0.04886231,0.08448047,-0.04471744,-0.03393551,0.02366065,-0.04587262,-0.01984472,-0.00836119,-0.03022581,0.00615516,-0.01257172,-0.00984532,0.04234223,0.06667953,0.08852375,-0.03013828,-0.00382636]',E'Step 2: Specify the Effect dependencies {/*step-2-specify-the-effect-dependencies*/}\n\n<Pitfall>\n\nThe behaviors without the dependency array and with an *empty* `[]` dependency array are different:\n\n```js {3,7,11}\nuseEffect(() => {\n  // This runs after every render\n});\n\nuseEffect(() => {\n  // This runs only on mount (when the component appears)\n}, []);\n\nuseEffect(() => {\n  // This runs on mount *and also* if either a or b have changed since the last render\n}, [a, b]);\n```\n\nWe''ll take a close look at what "mount" means in the next step.\n\n</Pitfall>\n\n<DeepDive>','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
