0.05858823,0.01166305,0.01388322,0.01782835,-0.01136837,0.02487451,0.05416526,-0.02427197,-0.01992502,0.02488177,0.01778866,0.01569124,-0.04596834,0.02894295,0.02487205,-0.01469376,0.00422876,-0.03878468,0.06964524,0.01160777,-0.02933541,0.05431525,-0.05442742,-0.02452667,0.00068476,-0.04494708,0.02910012,-0.00093141,-0.00974580,-0.02982312,-0.03676214,-0.01368237,0.01714621,0.01501666,-0.04888679,-0.01502037,0.03296655,0.01641480,-0.03207668,0.01911842,-0.03980066,-0.00475385]',E'Controlling non-React widgets {/*controlling-non-react-widgets*/}\n\nSometimes you need to add UI widgets that aren''t written in React. For example, let''s say you''re adding a map component to your page. It has a `setZoomLevel()` method, and you''d like to keep the zoom level in sync with a `zoomLevel` state variable in your React code. Your Effect would look similar to this:\n\n```js\nuseEffect(() => {\n  const map = mapRef.current;\n  map.setZoomLevel(zoomLevel);\n}, [zoomLevel]);\n```','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
