7934774,0.07551105,0.04709920,0.03530550,0.00039877,-0.00010230,0.03030920,0.05391988,-0.05568849,-0.07423140,0.01404866,0.00567560,-0.00985080,-0.09212296,-0.02164381,0.05823812,-0.01589050,-0.03385278,-0.06323275,0.11213902,-0.02871604,-0.06188936,0.06492005,-0.04488948,-0.03208514,0.02139675,0.00987213,0.02102391,0.00500356,-0.01216330,-0.00513182,-0.04607614,-0.03580068,0.00286488,-0.00477944,-0.01625339,0.00695334,0.00091374,0.03130651,-0.01751913,0.05972488,-0.01842345,0.05352228]',E'Controlling non-React widgets {/*controlling-non-react-widgets*/}\n\nSome APIs may not allow you to call them twice in a row. For example, the [`showModal`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLDialogElement/showModal) method of the built-in [`<dialog>`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLDialogElement) element throws if you call it twice. Implement the cleanup function and make it close the dialog:\n\n```js {4}\nuseEffect(() => {\n  const dialog = dialogRef.current;\n  dialog.showModal();\n  return () => dialog.close();\n}, []);\n```','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
