,0.19760105,0.10159633,0.03258917,-0.02761699,-0.04408785,0.02327964,-0.02692089,0.07020607,-0.01134569,-0.01299717,0.05132221,-0.04685137,-0.00590376,-0.06754026,-0.06713501,0.02446065,0.03932071,-0.03440903,-0.01465613,0.00749853,-0.05064064,-0.00821627,0.09336035,-0.03847970,0.00147113,-0.02821366,-0.09339815,0.00250381,0.01406638,-0.01885887,0.00308827,0.00686408,-0.02379671,-0.00290572,-0.08356653,0.02859393,0.03520891,0.01878376,0.04331000,0.03901700,0.04651760,0.00444790,0.02451253]',E'Not an Effect: Buying a product {/*not-an-effect-buying-a-product*/}\n\nYou wouldn''t want to buy the product twice. However, this is also why you shouldn''t put this logic in an Effect. What if the user goes to another page and then presses Back? Your Effect would run again. You don''t want to buy the product when the user *visits* a page; you want to buy it when the user *clicks* the Buy button.','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
