,0.17195657,0.02016290,0.03280850,0.03858464,-0.03303922,-0.02886153,0.04409404,0.09150922,-0.01550783,0.03847425,0.05380694,-0.02876887,0.06825990,-0.03106688,-0.01966260,0.01448883,-0.01659007,-0.01130894,-0.03407682,0.01636827,0.07662693,-0.00422134,0.04278984,-0.02657831,0.01369794,0.01202891,-0.10942712,-0.03458429,-0.03711487,-0.00514328,0.02615200,-0.02188110,0.01391476,0.01325768,-0.04245311,0.02907290,0.00511968,-0.02201405,0.04688700,0.00907296,0.11810371,-0.03715659,0.00326650]',E'Initial render {/*initial-render*/}\n\nThe user visits `<ChatRoom roomId="general" />`. Let''s [mentally substitute](/learn/state-as-a-snapshot#rendering-takes-a-snapshot-in-time) `roomId` with `''general''`:\n\n```js\n  // JSX for the first render (roomId = "general")\n  return <h1>Welcome to general!</h1>;\n```\n\n**The Effect is *also* a part of the rendering output.** The first render''s Effect becomes:\n\n```js\n  // Effect for the first render (roomId = "general")\n  () => {\n    const connection = createConnection(''general'');\n    connection.connect();\n    return () => connection.disconnect();\n  },\n  // Dependencies for the first render (roomId = "general")\n  [''general'']\n```\n\nReact runs this Effect, which connects to the `''general''` chat room.','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
