0.18617319,0.06055600,0.00307744,0.02965862,0.06398277,0.05290330,0.09532756,0.02573583,-0.10166842,-0.07548173,-0.00177413,0.05524966,-0.00424315,0.01577488,-0.02425965,0.03618719,0.01737882,-0.01108436,-0.03433573,0.03253124,0.01557327,-0.01116470,0.09765783,-0.04255670,-0.06007247,-0.01455577,0.01302675,0.04644798,-0.05626363,-0.04577768,0.02495416,-0.02727045,-0.04578063,0.02130776,-0.04644784,0.02317500,0.03754276,0.00902641,0.02549821,-0.01501939,0.11255258,-0.03530626,0.03428455]',E'Fix an interval that fires twice {/*fix-an-interval-that-fires-twice*/}\n\nThis `Counter` component displays a counter that should increment every second. On mount, it calls [`setInterval`.](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/setInterval) This causes `onTick` to run every second. The `onTick` function increments the counter.\n\nHowever, instead of incrementing once per second, it increments twice. Why is that? Find the cause of the bug and fix it.\n\n<Hint>','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
