0,0.07419905,0.01781077,0.00208579,0.00254319,-0.01134984,0.04206473,-0.00820118,-0.03376311,0.04754161,0.00368073,0.01296919,0.01468935,-0.01268783,-0.04564353,0.04196948,0.02643056,-0.00337111,-0.03068462,0.05627373,0.00382091,-0.02960235,0.01375347,-0.07725185,-0.00825758,0.00204609,-0.03174259,0.03785682,-0.02897194,-0.00218768,0.00903472,-0.05838823,0.00166213,0.03984990,-0.07786041,0.01842773,0.00693841,0.06412642,0.02975904,-0.02573673,0.02374815,-0.00696808,0.01039769]',E'Fix fetching inside an Effect {/*fix-fetching-inside-an-effect*/}\n\n- Selecting `''Bob''` triggers `fetchBio(''Bob'')`\n- Selecting `''Taylor''` triggers `fetchBio(''Taylor'')` **and cleans up the previous (Bob''s) Effect**\n- Fetching `''Taylor''` completes *before* fetching `''Bob''`\n- The Effect from the `''Taylor''` render calls `setBio(''This is Taylor’s bio'')`\n- Fetching `''Bob''` completes\n- The Effect from the `''Bob''` render **does not do anything because its `ignore` flag was set to `true`**','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Synchronizing With Effects", "section_title": "synchronizing-with-effects", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/synchronizing-with-effects.md", "topics": "react,hooks,synchronizing,with,effects", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
