39,0.03019213,0.04788697,0.04416678,-0.00875080,0.00171067,0.08278008,0.01430389,-0.03988120,-0.02757990,0.01465565,-0.03689208,-0.00696197,-0.03209473,0.01880712,-0.01493856,0.03639710,-0.03922042,-0.05470005,0.00246671,-0.02039721,0.04192222,0.06246646,-0.03466108,-0.00100346,-0.03975512,-0.11874330,-0.00412192,-0.00953370,0.01254592,0.02061481,-0.07117474,0.02499120,-0.06309182,-0.00965168,-0.01466873,-0.00832386,-0.02227481,0.03310719,0.06773615,0.06071390,0.01671366,0.06612844]',E'Adding a ref to your component {/*adding-a-ref-to-your-component*/}\n\nYou can add a ref to your component by importing the `useRef` Hook from React:\n\n```js\nimport { useRef } from ''react'';\n```\n\nInside your component, call the `useRef` Hook and pass the initial value that you want to reference as the only argument. For example, here is a ref to the value `0`:\n\n```js\nconst ref = useRef(0);\n```\n\n`useRef` returns an object like this:\n\n```js\n{\n  current: 0 // The value you passed to useRef\n}\n```','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Referencing Values With Refs", "section_title": "referencing-values-with-refs", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/referencing-values-with-refs.md", "topics": "react,hooks,referencing,values,with,refs", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
