3443,0.04278659,0.00693059,0.00889073,-0.01847132,-0.02544965,0.09084868,0.04023189,-0.06992727,-0.02760911,0.04209002,0.02084246,0.00604939,-0.05176202,-0.01032224,0.02475063,0.05647804,-0.00959715,-0.02344287,0.05979497,0.02020411,0.01997792,0.10303105,-0.10586363,-0.04077459,0.03186471,-0.06170848,-0.01332550,-0.00315100,-0.02908706,-0.00286678,-0.05707400,-0.02074484,0.04366490,-0.04477091,-0.01083325,-0.03498220,-0.01869051,0.04821708,-0.04725509,0.08283637,0.00718418,0.05457180]',E'Fix a component failing to re-render {/*fix-a-component-failing-to-re-render*/}\n\nThis button is supposed to toggle between showing "On" and "Off". However, it always shows "Off". What is wrong with this code? Fix it.\n\n<Sandpack>\n\n```js {expectedErrors: {''react-compiler'': [10]}}\nimport { useRef } from ''react'';\n\nexport default function Toggle() {\n  const isOnRef = useRef(false);\n\n  return (\n    <button onClick={() => {\n      isOnRef.current = !isOnRef.current;\n    }}>\n      {isOnRef.current ? ''On'' : ''Off''}\n    </button>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n</Sandpack>\n\n<Solution>','{"source": "react", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Referencing Values With Refs", "section_title": "referencing-values-with-refs", "url": "https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/referencing-values-with-refs.md", "topics": "react,hooks,referencing,values,with,refs", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
